title: Watch Future Stunt On Everyone In Video For 'Super Trapper' | DJ Clue | Power 105.1 FM
text:
share 
With Future's self titled album only dropping a couple of days ago the Atlanta rapper is waisting no time giving fans the first visual for the album. 
In this visual for "Super Trapper" Future is strictly stunting in a huge mansion with Girls, Cash, and plenty of ice. 
As is has already been decided by the internet that Future's new album is straight fire we can't wait to get more visuals for the album. 
Check out the video for "Super Trapper" below. ON AIR: Weekdays 6PM-10PM DJ Clue, is a Mixtape DJ known for his involvement in the Mixtape circuit and for being one of the first DJ's to not mix songs in his mixtapes. Clue is also known for dubbing both the song information and his name over each track on his mixtapes, usually in a distinctively echoed voice.He also has his own record label Desert Storm Records. Rappers Fabolous, Ransom and Paul Cain are among the artists with Desert Storm Records.Clue was hired to produce remixes of three of Mariah Carey's most recent and biggest hits: "We Belong Together", "Shake It Off", and "Don't Forget About Us". He subsequently had a featured DJ role in Carey's 2006 The Adventures of Mimi Tour. Back in 1999, DJ Clue has produced the extremely awaited Heartbreaker Remix featuring Missy Elliott and Da Brat for Carey's '99 album Rainbow. He is part of the Power 105.1fm family. Holding down the nights from 6-10pm Monday through Friday. Contact
